            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/12–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-23T18:00:00-05:00">December 23, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1876. Urtel 2536 Dec 16. While Dept opinion unilateral statement US re Comms
                    failure provide normal communication facilities Mukden would be of doubtful
                    efficacy restoring communications, believes joint approach those Govts having
                    consular establishments Mukden might have some effect. Emb therefore authorized
                    your discretion discuss question informally Brit French Embs Nanking view
                    possible release joint statement. Keep Dept informed and submit any agreed text
                    Dept’s review and approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
